explanation: [0-0] Beside a busy city road, a man is preparing to jump over a small canal. There is a lot of traffic on the road, and the roadside has green belts with tall trees and lawns. Four flags are hanging on four flagpoles arranged in a row. There is a person on each side of the man watching his actions. The wall of the river is connected to a steel structure, and there is turbid sewage below. The man is shirtless, wearing shorts, and making swinging arm movements.

[0-7] The man starts to jump, successfully jumps to the first beam, and immediately jumps over the second beam. When he jumps to the third beam, he doesn't land properly. The man supports himself with both hands on the beam and then falls into the mud of the river. The man struggles in the mud, trying to sit up. Then the camera zooms in for a close-up of the man, who is still struggling to stand up.
